parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights turn off randomly
one or both headlights do not work
headlights work intermittently
voltage issues at the rear plug of the headlight assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the auto stop/start feature can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at intersections or on highways.
symptoms: Vehicle shuts off without warning
engine dies
power steering fails
vehicle stalls
auto stop/start feature malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including engine stalling, loss of power steering, and failure of essential systems, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine shuts off
power steering fails
vehicle stalls
electrical issues with the starter
batteries
and alternator
radio and backup camera malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting off can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Engine shuts off
vehicle stalls
loss of power
coolant temperature warning
engine dies.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes oil at an alarming rate
requiring frequent oil additions
the low oil pressure light comes on
the engine stalls or shuts off while driving
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting off can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
the vehicle may experience a loss of power
the low oil pressure light comes on
and the vehicle may stall or shut off while idling or at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Coolant system issues can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The coolant temperature light comes on
the engine overheats
and the vehicle may stall or shut off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission temperature warning light is illuminated
the vehicle jerks or hesitates when shifting gears
the check engine light is on
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, overheating, and potentially cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
the oil level is low
the check engine light is on
and the vehicle may stall or shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the dashboard lights flicker or go out
the check engine light is on
and the vehicle may experience issues with the start/stop system
transmission
and other electrical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shutting off of the engine can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic, and can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off or stalls while driving
often without warning
and may not restart immediately. This can occur at any speed
including while idling at a red light or stop sign.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frequent occurrence of the "Coolant Temperature High" warning can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Coolant Temperature High" warning appears on the dashboard
often accompanied by the temperature gauge rising to the maximum level. The vehicle may shut down or decelerate suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents due to engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes oil at an excessive rate
requiring frequent oil changes before the recommended mileage. The check engine light may also illuminate
indicating low oil pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the touchscreen can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents, and may also interfere with the vehicle's safety features.
symptoms: The touchscreen display begins to delaminate
causing "phantom touches" or erratic behavior
such as launching apps or changing settings without user input.
